node.text:
Last week’s hand twisters:
Now the same engineers commonly still stay at the party to play and measure the wrong yellow cow.
When different friends have opposite goals conflicts are complicated. But then the same random arguments can’t hurt because it’s finally really right!
I like dry summer because black sky combined with white clouds make gray storms wet.

node.text:
This week, i did my first lachés since my 2 shoulder surgeries.  I’ve been rehabbing, strength training, and slow progressions, but it’s so fun to finally go for a few more dynamic moves!  It cracks me up every time I get nervous and bail, but I’m trying to respect those instincts and take it slow.  So after 2 days of obstacle training, nothing hurts! And I’m starting to feel like myself again. Thank you @arnold_h18 !!!
#americanninjawarrior #rotatorcuffrepair #wecanrebuildher

node.text:
Making use of all 18 g of protein in @lennyandlarrys “the Boss Cookie” to build and repair my muscles after this explosive workout.  To test your max cookie jump, measure the height of your mouth.  Then raise the cookie to see how high you can jump and take a bite out of it.  I maxed out at 23”. ... until next time, #theBossCookie!
Thank you to my assistants @kellyinmotion @darrenbailey17 and Stanley!

node.text: What an incredible adventure! Trying to stand up on a slack line 180 feet above a rocky river gorge was so hard and so much fun!  I have an even greater appreciation for this skill, and am newly inspired to rig up a slackline in my yard, so i can practice standing up from a seated position!  I didn’t get it this time, but i had so much fun falling and got a killer workout scrambling back up every one of the fifty million times that i fell!  Thank you so much Ryan for taking us out and keeping us safe!  And thank you @jannabreslin for filming!

node.text:
I had such an amazing day of climbing and learning Sign Language with @deafclimber @thedeafninja and so many new friends including climbing legend @campbellclimb and @julietclimbs!!! Thank you all so much for teaching me!!! Thanks for the photo @brianmikecole and for teaching me how to sign #adventure !
#ASLClimbingNetwork

@mlabninja

node.text:
I was scared, but i did it! 3 rungs on the #salmonladder at @mlabninja with no pain.  It’s like rediscovering a part of me that was lost!
*this is 8 months after my left shoulder and 11 months after my right shoulder surgery.  Check out yesterday’s post to see some beginner progressions and my first fearful attempt at a single rung ☺️
#shoulderrecovery #rotatorcuffrepair #americanninjawarrior #ninjawarrior
